<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Construction Progress Report</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            background-color: #031c00;
            color: #8ee28e;
        }
        .container {
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: 20px auto;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 5px;
            box-shadow: 0 2px 5px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }
        h1, h2 {
            text-align: center;
        }
        .progress {
            text-align: center;
            margin-top: 20px;
            display: grid;
            justify-content: center;
        }
        .progress-bar {
            width: 300px;
            height: 20px;
            background-color: #384336;
            border-radius: 10px;
            overflow: hidden;
            margin-bottom: 3px;
        }
        .progress-bar-inner {
            width: 59%;
            height: 100%;
            background-color: #4caf50;
            border-radius: 10px;
            transition: width 0.5s ease-in-out;
        }
        .progress-percent {
            margin-top: 5px;
        }
        .details {
            margin-top: 20px;
        }
        .details p {
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Construction Progress Report</h1>
        <div class="progress">
            <div class="progress-bar">
                <div class="progress-bar-inner"></div>
            </div>
            <div class="progress-percent">59% Complete</div>
        </div>
        <div class="details">
            <h2>Details:</h2>
            <p><strong>Project Name:</strong> Metro Expansion Line 3B</p>
            <p><strong>Location:</strong> City Center, Capital City</p>
            <p><strong>Current Phase:</strong> Rock and Soil Layout Analysis for Underground Tunnel Schematics</p>
            <p><strong>Current Progress:</strong> The analysis of rock and soil layout is 59% complete. Geologists have completed initial assessments of the soil composition and are now conducting detailed surveys of rock formations.</p>
            <p><strong>Next Steps:</strong> Complete the remaining soil composition assessments and finalize the detailed surveys of rock formations. Begin drafting the underground tunnel schematics based on the analysis results.</p>
            <p><strong>Expected Completion:</strong> The entire project is scheduled to be completed by Q4 2287.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
